RADAR
=====

The radar command sweeps your radar sectors and reveals terrain
in a radius around each one, updating your fog-of-war map.

COMMAND
-------
  radar SECT-SPEC     Sweep radar sector(s) matching SECT-SPEC
  radar *             Sweep all your radar sectors

  This command sweeps from radar STATION sectors only.  A land unit
  with radar capability sweeps with the separate 'lradar' command
  instead — see 'info lradar'.

SECTOR TYPE
-----------
  )   Radar  — the sector type that performs the sweep.
               Must be owned by you and ≥60% efficient to fire.

RANGE
-----
  Range is determined by your technology level and the sector's
  efficiency:

    range = floor( 16 * (50 + tech) / (200 + tech) * eff / 100 )
    minimum range: 1

  At tech 0, 100% efficient radar: range = floor(16 * 50/200) = 4
  At tech 200, 100%: range = floor(16 * 250/400) = 10
  At tech 500, 100%: range = floor(16 * 550/700) = 12
  Maximum (very high tech, 100%): approaches 16.

WHAT YOU SEE
------------
  The radar map uses the same character set as the sector map.
  Within range/3 of the radar:   actual sector mnemonic
  Beyond range/3 (outer ring):   '?' (something is there)
  Own sectors, sea (~), mountains (^), wasteland (+):
                                  always show actual mnemonic

  The center radar sector is marked '0' on the display.

FOG OF WAR
----------
  Empire uses fog of war: you only see sectors you have explored
  or swept with radar.  The `map` command shows your last-known
  view of all sectors.  Radar updates that view for the area
  scanned.

  Sectors you have never seen show as blank space on the map.
  Previously seen sectors show their last-known designation.

EXAMPLES
--------
  radar *          Sweep all your radar sectors.
  radar 4,4        Sweep only the radar at 4,4.
  radar #1         Sweep radar sectors in realm 1.

TIPS
----
  • A chain of radar sectors can map a wide area each update.
  • Higher tech dramatically extends range.
  • Keep radar sectors well-supplied and building toward 100%
    efficiency for maximum range.
  • Ships and planes can scout too — their movement updates your
    bmap as they travel.

